item.description:
wontfix: <p>
What about when you are on a taxonomy page and use 'pre_get_posts' to set an author etc. etc.? We can't apply band-aids like this.
</p>
<p>
You can reset <code>$wp_query-&gt;queried_object</code> to whatever you need, without modifying Core:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">function change_queried_object() {
  global $wp_query;
  if ( is_post_type_archive() )
    $wp_query-&gt;queried_object = get_post_type_object( get_post_type() );
}
add_action( 'template_redirect', 'change_queried_object' );
</pre>
